cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

The paper deals with deep learning for medical imaging data, specifically for survival time regression of patients with high grade brain tumors. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper compares deep learning approaches with classical regression methods, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The use of hand-crafted features and radiomic features suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of Support Vector Classifier (SVC) suggests that the paper may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the use of non-imaging clinical patient information suggests that the paper may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
